The biggest UX mistake developer tools make:
They explain before demonstrating.

Users don’t want:

explanations
technical context
feature lists

They want:

immediate interaction
instant results
visual confidence

Your /7f57ca page already does this better because:

the palette is the hero
the output is visible immediately
there’s less cognitive overhead

That’s closer to how successful tools behave.



It asks users to:
understand the product first

But great utility tools let users:
experience the product first

